You are an expert annotator of fictional narrative texts. You are given a GROUP of surface forms that an automatic clustering step claims ALL name ONE single in-story entity. Your job is to catch over-merging ("black hole" clusters that swallowed distinct characters via a chain of weak links).

Identify any surface forms that actually refer to a **different** entity and do NOT belong in this group.

Be conservative: only flag a form as an outlier if you are confident it names a different entity. If the whole group is coherent (one entity under several names/titles), return an empty list.

# Output

Return JSON only:

```json
{"outliers": ["surface form that does not belong", "..."]}
```

List the exact surface-form strings as given. Empty list if the group is coherent.
